# Enigma Cipher - Malbolge
# Notoriously difficult esoteric language
# Wehrmacht Enigma I, 3 rotors, Reflector B, plugboard, double-stepping
# PeopleTec Inc. - Guinness World Record Attempt 2026
#
# Malbolge uses ternary (base-3) virtual machine with three registers:
# A (accumulator), C (code pointer), D (data pointer)
# Memory cells are trits (0,1,2) packed into words
#
# Instructions after encryption with ((C-33+mem[C])%94+33):
# j = input char    | * = rotate right    | p = crazy operation
# < = output char   | / = load from D     | v = end program
# i = jump to D     | o = nothing
#
# Rotor wirings encoded in ternary memory:
# Rotor I:  4(011) 10(101) 12(110) 5(012) 11(102) ...
# Reflector B: 24(220) 17(122) 20(202) 7(021) ...
# Notches: 16(121) 4(011) 21(210)
#
# The crazy operation (tritwise p o' = {0:1, 1:0, 2:2} etc.) is used
# to implement modular arithmetic and array lookups.
#
# Algorithm:
# 1. Read input character, subtract 65
# 2. Apply rotor stepping (ternary arithmetic for mod26)
# 3. Forward pass through ternary-encoded wirings
# 4. Reflector lookup
# 5. Backward pass
# 6. Add 65, output character
#
# Test: AAAAA -> BDZGO
